-- Chaplains
('Chaplain Ed Hall',       'BCSO',     '530-990-5622', 'ehall@buttecounty.net',           'Edward Hall became the Senior Chaplain for Butte County Sheriff''s Office in 2017 and serves as Senior Pastor of Wynn Memorial Church in Oroville. He previously served with the US Navy for six years during the Desert Storm Era. Certifications include CISM, Suicide Prevention, Death Notification, Officer Involved Shooting Debrief, and EMDR Level 1. He served as team leader for CARE during the Camp Fire (2018–2019).',                                                                                     'Lead Chaplain · BCSO · Critical Incident Stress Management Team',                                                                                                                  true,  1),
('Chaplain Ken Malone',    'BCSO',     '530-282-3313', null,                              'Chaplain Ken Malone has been the Pastor of New Life Church in Oroville for 24 years and currently serves as a Chaplain for BCSO. Born in Denver, Colorado, he moved to Oroville in 1976. He loves his family, the outdoors, fishing, hunting, and camping.',                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           'BCSO Chaplain',                                                                                                                                                                     true,  2),
('Chaplain Josh Cook',     'BCSO',     null,           'jcook@buttecounty.net',           'Chaplain Josh Cook was sworn in as a BCSO Chaplain in March 2022. He served 9 years in the California State Guard, attaining the rank of Staff Sergeant. He is ordained in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and is an Associate Professor at the University of Southern California Price School of Public Policy. His areas of expertise include marriage and family counseling, emergency management, disaster recovery, and response to moral injury and trauma.',                                        'BCSO Chaplain · Marriage & Family Counseling · Emergency Management · Trauma Response',                                                                                            true,  3),
('Chaplain Brian Dudar',   'BCSO',     '530-520-4112', 'bdudar@buttecounty.net',          'Brian Dudar spent 11 years in youth ministry, along with 13 years as an Army Chaplain ministering to combat and hospital units. He received his Master''s in Divinity from Andrews University in 1993. He currently serves as the Dental Director of Northern Valley Indian Health. He joined BCSO as a chaplain in May 2017 and was involved in chaplain coverage during the Camp Fire.',                                                                                                                                'BCSO Chaplain · Army Chaplain · Suicide Prevention · Critical Incident Counseling · Trauma',                                                                                       true,  4);


